The initial modeling focused on selecting a base model structure without incorporating any covariates. Linear 2- (ADVAN3, TRANS4) and 3-compartment (ADVAN11, TRANS4) PK models with first order elimination were evaluated. Inter-individual variability (IIV) and between-occasion variability (BOV) random effects were included in the base model and assumed to be log-normally distributed. For example, the value of model parameter P after the kth dose administered to the ith individual, P
i,k, is\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
