				\begin{document}$$ P_{i,k} = P_{TV} \times e^{{(n_{i}^{(P)} + \kappa_{i,k}^{(P)} )}} $$\end{document}where P
TV is the typical value of the model parameter, η
i(P) is the inter-individual variability, and κ
i,k(P) is the between-occasion variability.

